Have you experienced your higher self?
-
Although it may sound like a lofty concept, technically speaking, the higher self is just the part of the brain that neuroscientists call the neocortex. It is the seat of imagination, empathy and impartial judgement.
-
More broadly, it is the part of our consciousness we access when we see life from a more universal, less biased point of view. We often experience this state of consciousness late at night or early in the morning, when there are no threats or demands upon us; our minds are quiet and our bodies comfortable. We go beyond our primal, survival-based thinking and experience a deeper sense of connection with the universe.
-
Have you experienced this state of consciousness before?

-
I continued posting quotes along with my own perspectives on a daily basis. To my surprise, other people started following my page!

When I say this, people often assume their excitement needs to be in the form of some grand idea or life passion. It doesn't.
-
What I literally mean is: get in touch with the small, everyday things that spark your interest or pique your curiosity. Then ACT on those things to the fullest extent that you possibly can. Repeat this process ad infinitum. That's where the magic is.
-
Why is this important? Because these little things are the breadcrumbs that will lead you to the bigger things (i.e. your purpose, passion, etc). This process has worked for me, for many people I've observed, and probably for many people whom you admire.
-
Here's the tricky part: many people don't know what excites them. This is largely because they‚Äôve ignored and suppressed their natural instinct to act on what excites them in the name of  being a "responsible adult."
-
If we want to create a magical life, we must abandon this way of thinking. The choice between being a "responsible adult" and doing what excites you is a false dichotomy. You can do both.
‚ÄîRuben #ThinkGrowProsper
